In live theater, you never know who will be in the audience...or backstage! I guess everyone had the same idea, to go see August Wilson's @thepianolessonplay last night cuz 🌟 was in the building ( on stage and in the seats) I count myself as one of them. Amazing work 👏🏾 👏🏾👏🏾 to the cast @samuelljackson @daniebb3  @traibyers @ray8fisher ...and yall know how I feel about @johndavidwashington 😉. The backstage was popping, all the actors like @jonathanmajors_ were there giving their praises, and I got to see Mrs Latanya @ltjackson_ and give her a big hug cuz I promised Id be back! SHE DIRECTED THAT THANG!!! So many beautiful, rich, layered, BLACK, moments and such loaded and complex language! But we as the audience were locked in. Thank you all. 
And thank you to my girl @cassiejanaywigs for the plug ! 😘

Repost @classicstage :
D. Woods simultaneously radiates hope, strength, exhaustion, joy, and unconditional love as the loyal Nella Pea Lincoln (Nella P), wife of Ulysses Lincoln and mother to their son, Malachai. 

Like the steadfast Penelope from The Odyssey, Nella’s dedication to her husband and son transcends all obstacles thrown her way, be it war, gods, in-laws, or… teenage shenanigans.

“I know so many Nella P's in my life, and exploring all the nuances of her circumstances and motives felt like a story that needs to be told. This show speaks to so many aspects of the African American experience. It's right on time for Black History month!!!” - @yagirldwoods

Don’t miss D. as Nella P! Tickets are available ➤ Link in Bio

D. Woods is a singer, songwriter, actress, and dancer. Follow D. @yagirldwoods 
 📸 Credit: Julieta Cervantes

Pt. 3 of my wrap up #BlackOdyssey dump.
I lost the love of my life, gave birth, raised a teenager, got engaged, and married every night on stage...WHAT AN EXPERIENCE! Nella Pea swam in some treacherous waters of emotion. Self Preservation vs. Love was a constant struggle in developing this character. Im honored to have had the opportunity to explore and create with artists doing the same fearless work everyday. And doing it all with Respect Encouragement and Comedy!  Until next time... 
FAMILY *** ENSEMBLE*** BLACK ODYSSEY 
#DREAMERS 
#WeAreOurAncestorsWildestDreams

Wow! It might have been April Fool's Day but we did not come to play!!!
1 year ago on this day April 1st 2022 I made my BROADWAY DEBUT in the revival of Ntzoke Shange’s "for colored girls..." at the Booth Theater. I can not describe the power, magic, anointing, fierceness, BLACK GIRL MAGIC that flowed through this cast and company!!! Just looking at these pics and videos got me fired up. Oh how I miss this group and show. WE DID THAT! Thank you Camille @camilleabrown thank you Ancestor Ntozake Shange, thank you to everyone who supported this production, bought a ticket, shared a post etc. Thank you to all the Original "for colored girls" cast members who gave us their beautiful blessing and passed the torch. And to @whostendayi @pbnj_hotter @staceysargeant @alexandriawailesofficial @bornokwui @minanina81 and our baby Nova Pearl @mckenziefrye @alexisjeanene @kalaross @treshelleedmond @cassiejanaywigs @deahlove our stage managers Ms. Bernita and Ms. lowercase lark my #YEA brother @justellington @jaylennn___ @maleek_washington @mayte_n @moraaminaparker Love yall HAPPY ANNIVERSARY #FCG GANG GANG 💛🧡❤💜💙💚🤎

Big Congrats to @natblacktheatre and the whole cast of @fathambway ! The way yall had me ROTFL 😆 last summer at @publictheaterny all the way to BROADWAY baby! BRAVO 👏🏾 Have an amazing run.

School is in session and Ya Girl D. WOODS has your required reading...or listening. 📖📕 🎧 Im so exicted that this summer I have been apart of 3 audiobooks and they are all available for your listening pleasure on Audible books and Amazon for the physical copies! First up #SHOWYOUNOMERCY by K. Powell @iamk.powell will have you gagging and clutching your pearls honey!!! I gave a GOoooood dramatic read for this murder mystery ! Second, its for the culture with the ladies of hiphop in #TheMotherlode by Clover Hope @clovito and some of EVERYBODY is in this audio telling of the ladies side of the hip hop history! Last but not least is #SINGABLACKGIRLSSONG the Unpublished posthumous collection of Ntozake Shange. Im honored to continue to be apart of her legacy and work after making my BROADWAY DEBUT in the 7 times TONY NOMINATED FORCOLOREDGIRLS in 2022. Sing a Black Girl’s Song is an extraordinary collection of unpublished works by the award-winning American literary icon Ntozake Shange. The anthology features essays, plays, and poems curated by National Book Award winner Imani Perry, and includes a foreword by New York Times bestselling author Tarana Burke. 

She's giving BOOKED...LITERALLY ! 😆

Its our baby's first day of school!!! As the great poet and spiritual vessel Erykah Badu @erykahbadu has said "Keep in mind that we are artist and we are sensitive about our 💩." We have cultivated and nurtured this sacred space and expression, combining our gifts, experiences, and hearts, its no wonder why this part of the journey is nerve racking and feels a bit invasive. As strangers enter the safe space we have created to free ourselves and discover in this work, it is my prayer that they will come as willing and open as we are. Theater is a communal exchange and this piece especially requires all parties to participate.
